omponent ...)` loop below.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The <code>core</code> directory is treated with the same logic as the component directories, so it should be added to the <code>CPPCHECK_DIRS</code> in the <code>foreach(component ...)</code> loop below.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-07-20T02:18:10.907246+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:67759e29-d1df-465f-868d-047738e36fc9/d42d74cf-c1bd-4431-8288-07f543bbe325/128"}}, "nickname": "mxgrey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:67759e29-d1df-465f-868d-047738e36fc9"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2018-07-20T02:18:35.495471+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 70526939}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 100, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/100.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/100"}}, "title": "Allow core library files to have their own directory"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/100/comments/70492539.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/100/_/diff#comment-70492539"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 100, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/100.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/100"}}, "title": "Allow core library files to have their own directory"}, "content": {"raw": "should update this codecheck logic to handle `core` as well", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>should update this codecheck logic to handle <code>core</code> as well</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-07-19T17:27:27.065894+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2018-07-19T17:27:27.075222+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 70492539}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 100, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/100.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/100"}}, "title": "Allow core library files to have their own directory"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/100/comments/70492404.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/100/_/diff#comment-70492404"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 100, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/100.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/100"}}, "title": "Allow core library files to have their own directory"}, "content": {"raw": "I think this is here because reconfiguring can change which tests are run, so it can be confusing to see test results for unrunnable tests. I do see your point though.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I think this is here because reconfiguring can change which tests are run, so it can be confusing to see test results for unrunnable tests. I do see your point though.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-07-19T17:26:02.350517+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2018-07-19T17:26:02.360927+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 70492404}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 100, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/100.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/100"}}, "title": "Allow core library files to have their own directory"}}, {"update": {"description": "Right now our file structure feels a little unbalanced to me. We have something like:\r\n\r\n    src/\r\n    include/\r\n    component1\r\n    -- src/\r\n    -- include/\r\n    component2\r\n    -- src/\r\n    -- include/\r\n    ...etc...\r\n\r\nThis PR allows ignition projects to \\(optionally\\) balance this out a bit by accepting the following directory structure:\r\n\r\n    core\r\n    -- src/\r\n    -- include/\r\n    component1\r\n    -- src/\r\n    -- include/\r\n    component2\r\n    -- src/\r\n    -- include/\r\n    ...etc...\r\n\r\n`gnition-cmake` will check for a top-level `core` directory, and if it fails to find that, it will expect a top-level `src` and `include` directory like what we\u2019ve been using.\r\n\r\nThis is a backwards-compatible and mostly superficial change. It\u2019s currently being used in the new [ign-plugin](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-plugin/src/NewRegistrationScheme/) repo, in case anyone wants to see so